&lt;h3 id="_ingredients"&gt;Ingredients&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;div class="sectionbody"&gt;

&lt;table class="tableblock frame-all grid-all stretch"&gt;

&lt;colgroup&gt;

&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;

&lt;col style="width: 50%;"&gt;

&lt;/colgroup&gt;

&lt;tbody&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 teaspoon plus 2 tablespoons butter, divided&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1-2/3 cups sugar&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2/3 cup evaporated milk&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1/2 teaspoon salt&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;2 cups miniature marshmallows&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 package (10 to 11 ounces) butterscotch chips&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;tr&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1/2 cup chopped walnuts, toasted&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;td class="tableblock halign-left valign-top"&gt;&lt;p class="tableblock"&gt;1 teaspoon maple flavoring&lt;/p&gt;&lt;/td&gt;

&lt;/tr&gt;

&lt;/tbody&gt;

&lt;/table&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;div class="sect1"&gt;

&lt;h3 id="_directions"&gt;Directions&lt;/h3&gt;

&lt;div class="sectionbody"&gt;

&lt;div class="olist arabic"&gt;

&lt;ol class="arabic"&gt;

&lt;li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Line an 8-in. square pan with foil and grease the foil with 1 teaspoon butter; set aside.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;In a large saucepan, combine the sugar, milk, salt and remaining 2 tablespoons butter.

Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture comes to a boil.

Boil for 5 minutes, stirring constantly.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Remove from heat; add the marshmallows, chips, nuts and maple flavoring.

Stir until marshmallows and chips are melted.

Spoon into prepared pan.

Let stand until set.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;li&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Using foil, lift fudge out of pan.

Discard foil; cut fudge into 1-in squares.

Store in an airtight container at room temperature.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;/li&gt;

&lt;/ol&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;/div&gt;

